cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the operation of a robotic mobile manipulator, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a novel algorithm that fuses a convolutional neural network with efficient point cloud processing for real-time grasping pose estimation from RGB-D images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a Bayesian framework for inferring the door kinematic model from observations of its motion while opening it and learning from previous experiences or human demonstrations, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the assistive human-centered behaviors of the robot, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
